# .gitattributes — line endings, decided here rather than by whoever cloned the repo.
#
# Everything in this project that starts a process is a bash script with a `#!` on line 1:
# the six root entry points, scripts/*.sh, and the container launcher. A shebang followed by
# a carriage return is not a shebang — the kernel looks for an interpreter literally named
# "/usr/bin/env bash\r" and reports "no such file or directory", naming neither the file it
# could not run nor the reason. That is the single most expensive way to spend an afternoon
# available in this repo.
#
# It is not hypothetical: `git config core.autocrlf true` is a common Windows default, WSL2's
# git inherits it from a Windows-side global config, and the supported Windows layout (a clone
# inside the WSL2 filesystem) still runs these scripts under Linux. Without this file that
# combination produces CRLF working-tree copies of every entry point.
#
# `text=auto` lets git decide what is text; `eol=lf` says that anything it decides IS text
# gets LF in the working tree on every platform, autocrlf or not. Binary files are detected
# and left alone — the explicit `-text` block below is belt-and-braces for the formats where
# a wrong guess would corrupt real content.

*               text=auto eol=lf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- executables
# Covered by the blanket rule above. Listed explicitly because these are the files where the
# failure is silent and unattributable, and because an explicit line survives someone
# loosening the blanket rule later.
init            text eol=lf
demo            text eol=lf
stop            text eol=lf
clean           text eol=lf
health          text eol=lf
docsite         text eol=lf
scripts/*.sh    text eol=lf

# The container lane, for when it lands: `cr` is the only thing a Windows user runs, and
# docker/entrypoint.sh is baked in as the image ENTRYPOINT, where a CRLF copy reproduces the
# same unfindable error from *inside* the container. Inert until those files exist.
cr              text eol=lf
docker/*.sh     text eol=lf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------- never touch these
*.png           -text
*.ico           -text
*.jpg           -text
*.jpeg          -text
*.mp4           -text
*.zip           -text
*.db            -text
*.xlsx          -text
